      • hasAccess

        public boolean hasAccess(Identity identity)
        Returns true if the identity has capabilities, rights or attributes which give them access to this resource. If the user has the SystemAdministrator capability or if this.allowAll() is true, access is always granted.
        Parameters:
        identity - Identity whose access is being checked.
        Returns:
        True if the identity is allowed to access this resource,
